<%# How it works — docs INDEX. Holds the brief, the TLDR and the chapter
    map; the depth lives in views/docs/* (one chapter per page, user
    direction 2026-06-12). Copy rule: simple words, no hyphens in visible
    text. The em dashes in .meta / .jp-sub strips are design furniture
    (字幕 pattern), not prose punctuation. %>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <%- include('partials/head', { title: 'How it works' }) %>
</head>
<body class="min-h-screen bg-paper font-sans text-ink antialiased">
  <%- include('partials/frame') %>
  <%- include('partials/nav') %>

  <main class="relative mx-auto max-w-6xl overflow-hidden px-6 py-12">
    <span class="pointer-events-none absolute -right-10 top-6 select-none font-serif text-[15rem] font-extrabold leading-none text-ink/[0.04]" aria-hidden="true">仕</span>

    <div class="reveal relative">
      <h1>
        <span class="relative inline-block font-serif text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight">
          <span class="absolute -inset-x-4 -inset-y-1.5 rotate-1 bg-sakura" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span class="relative text-paper">仕組み</span>
        </span>
        <span class="jp-sub mt-3">shikumi — how your recommendations are made</span>
      </h1>

      <%# ——— The brief ——— %>
      <div class="mt-10 max-w-3xl space-y-5 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink/85">
        <p>
          <strong>The brief</strong> — the whole idea in one breath. Open any
          anime page and a list called <span class="text-sakura">赤い糸</span>,
          the red thread, appears under the synopsis. It is built by a small
          engine that lives on this site. The engine reads what every anime
          in the catalog is <em>about</em>, measures how alike two shows are
          from several independent angles, lets those measurements vote, and
          shows you the winners. No account, no tracking, no cloud service.
          These pages explain every part of it in plain words.
        </p>
      </div>

      <%# ——— The TLDR ——— %>
      <h2 class="mt-14">
        <span class="font-serif text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight">要約</span>
        <span class="jp-sub">youyaku — the TLDR, the whole system in five lines</span>
      </h2>
      <ol class="mt-6 max-w-3xl space-y-px border border-ink/15 bg-ink/15">
        <li class="flex gap-4 bg-paper p-4">
          <span class="font-serif text-lg font-extrabold text-ink/30">1</span>
          <p class="text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink/85">Over <span class="tabular-nums">38,000</span> anime live in our own database: titles, two summaries each, tags, genres, studios, years, formats and how they all relate.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4 bg-paper p-4">
          <span class="font-serif text-lg font-extrabold text-ink/30">2</span>
          <p class="text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink/85">A small language model turns every summary into a fingerprint of its meaning, so stories can match by what they say, not by the words they use.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4 bg-paper p-4">
          <span class="font-serif text-lg font-extrabold text-ink/30">3</span>
          <p class="text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink/85">Eight signals vote on every candidate: story, tags, genres, studio, era, length, source material and format. Votes are scaled and added up.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4 bg-paper p-4">
          <span class="font-serif text-lg font-extrabold text-ink/30">4</span>
          <p class="text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink/85">A checkpoint removes the franchise of the show you are viewing, so the list is reserved for new things, never its own sequels.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4 bg-paper p-4">
          <span class="font-serif text-lg font-extrabold text-ink/30">5</span>
          <p class="text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink/85">You hold the slider that mixes the votes, and every pick names the signals that found it. If it cannot explain itself, it does not ship.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <%# ——— The chapters ——— %>
      <h2 class="mt-14">
        <span class="font-serif text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight">目次</span>
        <span class="jp-sub">mokuji — the chapters, one part each</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink/85">
        The depth lives in four short chapters. Read them in order, or jump
        to the part you are curious about.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-px border border-ink/15 bg-ink/15 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <% chapters.forEach((c) => { %>
        <a href="/how-it-works/<%= c.slug %>" class="group bg-paper p-6">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-3">
            <span class="meta"><%= c.num %> · <%= c.kanji %> — <%= c.reading %></span>
            <span class="meta text-ink/40 transition-colors group-hover:text-sakura">→</span>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-2 font-serif text-xl font-extrabold tracking-tight transition-colors group-hover:text-sakura"><%= c.title %></p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink/60"><%= c.tease %></p>
        </a>
        <% }) %>
      </div>

      <p class="meta mt-8">model — minilm, 384 numbers per fingerprint, runs on our own machine · math — cosine similarity, weighted votes · no account, no tracking, nothing about you is collected</p>
    </div>
  </main>

  <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
